===Etymology===
From [[Middle English]], from [[Old English]] [[hors]].

===Pronunciation===
* {{AHD|hô(r)s}}, {{IPA|/hɔː(r)s/}}, {{SAMPA|/hO:(r)s/}}
*{{audio|en-us-horse.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*:Homophones: [[hoarse]]
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɔː(r)s|-ɔː(r)s]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A large hoofed [[animal]] (scientific name ''[[Equus caballus]]'').
#:''A cowboy's greatest friend is his '''horse'''.''
# (''Zoology'') Any current or extinct animal of the family Equidae, including the [[zebra]] or the [[ass]].
#:''These bone features, distinctive in the zebra, are actually present in all '''horses'''.''
# ''(uncountable)'' Cavalry soldiers.
#:''We should place two units of '''horse''' and one of foot on this side of the field.''
# A piece of equipment with a body on two or four legs, approximately four feet high with two handles on top, used in gymnastics.
#:''She's scored very highly with the parallel bars, let's see how she does with the '''horse'''.''
# (''chess''; ''rare'') A knight.
#:''Now just remind me how the '''horse''' moves again?''
# {{slang}} Heroin.
#:''Alright, mate, got any '''horse'''?''
# (''slang''; ''offensive'') A Tongan.

